Add this one to the orbiter category:

Deimos http://kerbalspaceprogram.com/forum/index.php?topic=8530.0

What distinguishes between light and medium orbiters? This one has about 1000 delta-V in the orbiter.

Main difference it the role rather than mass or anything. light orbiters are designs that pretty much just enough to get into orbit and back down, while medium orbiters are designs with fuel for lots of orbital manoeuvres. Nice little design, how well does it glide?

Nice little design, how well does it glide?

Glide? That\'s why there\'s the decoupler, lol. That rocket and my new Phoenix II are designed for looks. You can add the Phoenix II to the heavy orbiter section.
Here is a Mun lander for 0.14 ONLY: http://kerbalspaceprogram.com/forum/index.php?topic=8096.0

Not much onto stock, but decided to give it a try, giving birth to the Craft series.

Q: What\'s up with the name?

A: I reserve notable names for rockets that deserve it.

Currently got 4 of the series. Will only show 2 here.

Craft01-MO (Modular Orbital)

Simple rocket to put you in LKO.

Craft02-MGEO (Modular Geostationary)

Basically a Craft01 with an extra upper stage, making it capable of going to GKO and higher orbits.

Craft03-E (Escape)

Basic rocket to get you out of Kerbin. (not shown)

Craft04-ML (Munar Landing)

My first stock Munar Lander. Work in progress. Already had a prototype.

Craft05-KE (Kerbol Escape)

Stock rocket capable of escaping Kerbol. Still on planning stage.

01 and 02 are attached.
